class Solution {
public:
    int numberOfSpecialChars(string word) {
        int count = 0;
        bool seenUpper = false;
        for (char c : word) {
            if (islower(c)) {
                if (seenUpper) {
                    break;
                }
            } else {
                seenUpper = true;
            }
            if (seenUpper) {
                count++;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the string once, keeping track of whether an uppercase occurrence of a character has been seen. If an uppercase occurrence is seen and a lowercase occurrence of the same character is encountered, the character is counted as special.

